rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all accounting metrics. Important subtypes of the collection include mso:finance.revenue and mso:finance.expense.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Accounting metric

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects data about the percentage that a given mso:finance.accounting_metric contributes to an entity's mso:finance.financial_performance. This allows an expense to be represented as part of the overall financial performance of a company.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Accounting Metric Percentage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.accounting_metric_percentage relationship to the mso:finance.accounting_metric for which the percentage holds true. For example, operational expenses are a given percentage of the total expenses.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Accounting Metric

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.accounting_metric_percentage relationship to the mso:measurement_unit.dated_percentage that collects data about the percentage and date of the financial metric for the given agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Percentage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all accounting services. These are the services focused on measurement, processing, and communication of financial entities. Included in this type are auditing services, tax services, and accounting forensics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Accounting Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A financial institution that offers both personal and commercial banking services, including checking accounts, saving accounts, loans, and credit card services.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bank

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all business insurance policies. Business insurance is a type of insurance protecting against the risk of damage to and destruction of commercial property, as well as the acts of fraudulent employees.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Business Insurance Policy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that specializes in collecting debts on behalf of companies or individuals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Collection Agency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all college financing services. These services include private services, like school loans provided by private banks, public services like government loans and grants, and saving vehicles like the 529 plans in the United States.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: College Financing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the concept of commercial banking. Commerical banking is defined as the set of deposit and loan services a bank or bank division provides to corporations or other large businesses. See also mso:finance.personal_banking for the set of banking services provided to individual consumers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commercial Banking

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of credit cards. Credit cards are the payment cards issued to users as a system of payment. The card allows the holder to pay for goods and services on the basis of a promise to pay the credit card company. Debt incurred by using credit cards is unsecured.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Credit Card

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all credit management services. Credit management includes the management of credit card debt and other lines of credit for consumers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Credit Management

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A medium of exchange issued by a sovereign government, especially banknotes and coins.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Currency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a currency to a country that used the currency in the past, but no longer does so.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Countries Formerly Used

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a currency to a country that currently uses the currency.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Countries Used

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a currency to the ISO 4217 designator for the currency. For example, the code for the Euro currency is EUR.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Currency Code

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a currency to the symbol for the currency that is customarily placed before am amount of the currency, e.g. $412 for 412 US Dollars.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Prefix Symbol

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The financial service of exchanging one currency for another, either as an investment or for travel purposes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Currency Exchange

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of currency subunits. These include things like the U.S. penny, which is a subunit of the US Dollar, and the euro coin, which is a subunit of the Euro.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Currency Subunit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.currency_subunit to the corresponding currency.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Currency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.currency_subunit to the date the currency subunit was issued.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Introduction Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.currency_subunit to the number of the subunit that equals one unit of the currency. For example, 100 U.S. pennies equal one US dollar.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quantity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.currency_subunit to the date the currency subunit was discontinued.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Revoked Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The financial service of holding money in a third-party account for agents that are completing a financial transaction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Escrow Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects data about the amount of one currency (the source) that can be exchanged for another currency (the target) on a given date.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Exchange Rate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the amount of target currency that is equal to one unit of the source currency.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Amount

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date for which the provided exchange rate is valid.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date of rate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the source currency of the given exchange rate.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Source of Exchange

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the target currency of the given exchange rate.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Target of Exchange

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of expenses. Expenses are those outflows of money from an agent to pay for goods or services. Expenses include instances like rent, tuition, and capital and financing expenses.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Expense

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type collecting data about the types and amounts of expenses that an agent may have. Common types of expenses include administrative expenses, operational expenses, and so forth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Expense Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.expense_relationship to the mso:event.agent for which the expense data is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Agent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating mso:organization.expense_relationship to the mso:measurement_unit.dated_money_value that collects the value and valid date for the given mso:finance.expense.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Expense Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finace.expense_relationship to the mso:finance.expense of the given agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Expense Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all farm insurance policies. Farm insurance is a type of insurance protecting against the risk of damage to or destruction of farms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Farm Insurance Policy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of institutions that collect funds and invest those funds in financial assets or make them available for direct lending.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Financial Institution

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a financial institution to the total market value of assets that the institution manages on behalf of investors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Assets under Management

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type collecting data on the financial performance of an mso:event.agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Financial Performance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.financial_performance to the mso:finance.accounting_metric_percentage collecting data based on the percentages of given mso:finance.accounting_metric
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Metric Percentage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.financial_performance to the fundraising efficiency for the mso:event.agent. Efficiency in this measure is the amount spent by the agent to raise $1 in contributions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fundraising Efficiency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.financial_performance to the mso:measurement_unit.dated_percentage that is the average annual growth of primary revenue for the agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Primary Revenue Growth

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.financial_performance to the mso:measurement_unit.dated_percentage that is the average annual growth of program expenses.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Program Expenses Growth

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.financial_performance to the agent's working capital ratio, which is the estimated length of time an agent could sustain its level of spending using its net available assets, or working capital, as most recently reported.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Working Capital Ratio

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all financial services. Financial services are those services provided by the finance industry. These services include mso:finance.loan, mso:finance.insurance_policy, and so forth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Financial Services

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all health insurance policies. Health insurance is a type of insurance protecting against the risk of medical expenses. The benefit may be administered by a centralized organization like a government or private business or it may be purchased by an individual.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Health Insurance Policy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all home insurance policies. Home insurance is a type of insurance protecting against the risk of damage to or destruction of a home, including personal property.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Home Insurance Policy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Income tax forms that are intended to be submitted. These are distinguished from finance.income_tax_schedules, which are not filed but are used to compute data entered on finance.income_tax_filing_forms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Income Tax Filing Forms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an income tax filing form to the date by which the form must be filed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Income Tax Form Deadline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an income tax filing form to information about how and where to file the form.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Income Tax Form Filing Information

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an income tax filing form to income tax schedules associated with the filing form.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Income Tax Form Schedule

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Forms that are issued by a government agency and are intended to be used for reporting income for tax purposes. Both filing forms and tax schedules are included in this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Income Tax Forms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an income tax form to a URL providing the form online.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Income Tax Form URL

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an income tax form to a URL providing instructions for completing the form.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Income Tax Form Instructions URL

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an income tax form to the government agency that produced the form and to which the form must be submitted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Income Tax Form Issuing Agency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an income tax form to a phone number associated with the tax form.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Income Tax Form Phone Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an income tax form to the year for which the form is to be used to report income.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Year of Income Tax Form

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Income tax forms that are are not filed but are used to compute data entered on finance.income_tax_filing_forms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Income Tax Schedules

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of insurance agencies. These are the businesses that specialize in insurance policies for purchase.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Insurance Agency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all insurance policies. Insurance policies are contracts between an insurer and an insured, also known as the policyholder, which determine the claims which the insurer is legally required to pay. In general, insurance is the transfer of the risk of loss from one entity to another in exchange for payment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Insurance Policy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an insurance policy to the agency that provides the policy.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Issuer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or institution that specializes in negotiating and overseeing investment transactions, particularly those involving stocks and bonds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Investment Broker

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A financial institution whose sole business is to provide loans to customers, e.g. payday loans.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lending Company

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all life insurance policies. A life insurance policy will pay a sum of money to a designated beneficiary on the death of the insured.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Life Insurance Policy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all loans. Loans are debt instruments that have a principal amount, interest rate, and date of repayment. Loans are the primary business of mso:finance.financial_institution. Bonds, in contrast to loans, are debt instruments that are issued by governments or companies and can be traded on a market.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Loan

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A currency that is a issued by a local organization without the backing of a sovereign and is accepted as tender only by designated enterprises in the locality.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Local Currency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a local currency to a location where the currency is used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A measure of the value of a particular sector of a stock market that is computed from the prices of a given pool of stocks, e.g. the Dow Jones Industrial Average.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Market Index

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The financial service of electronically moving an amount of currency from one location to another.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Money Transfer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all mortgage loans. Mortgage loans are those types of loans secured by real estate.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mortgage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or establishment that specializes in brokering or providing real estate loans.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mortgage Broker Lender

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Institutions that provide loans for a relatively small amount of money that are secured by items of personal property that can be sold if the loan is not repaid.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pawn Shop

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the concept of personal banking. Personal banking involves transactions of financial institutions directly with consumers. The services provided include saving and transactional accounts, consumer loans for mortgages and vehicles, and the provision of credit and debit cards.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Personal Banking

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of personal finance services, which are financial services that focus on how an individual or family obtains, budgets, saves, and spends monetary resources.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Personal Finance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all personal investment services, which are services that allow an individual or family to invest in assets with the goal of capital appreciation, dividends, or interest earnings.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Personal Investing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all personal loans. Personal loans are loans that are not collateralized by a lien on specific assets of the borrower. In the event of bankruptcy, unsecured creditors will have a general claim on the assets of the borrower after the secured creditors. Examples of unsecured debt include credit card debt, medical bills, payday loans, and term deposits.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Personal Loan

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration type representing the different kinds of pricing models, including instances such as free, subscription, and freemium.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pricing Model

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the free pricing models.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Free

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration representing the freemium pricing model, the model that offers some content for free while charging a fee for premium services and features.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Freemium

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value applying to content, such that the buyer has unlimted access to the content.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pay per Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value applying to content, such that the buyer has a right to view the content only once.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pay per View

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value representing the premium model, the model that offers a product or service for a fee.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pay per View

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration representing the subscription pricing models.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subscription

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all retirement planning services, whose goal is to accumulate a set of assets that can be distributed when work income ceases or diminishes later in life.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Retirement Planning

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of revenue. Revenue is the income for an agent before any deductions are taken. Instances of revenue include income, gifts, and contributions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Revenue

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data about the amounts and types of revenue for a given agent. Profit, gifts, endowments are all examples of revenue an agent may have.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Revenue Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.revenue_relationship to the mso:event.agent with this revenue.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Agent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.revenue_relationship to the mso:finance.revenue type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Revenue Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:finance.revenue_relationship to the amount of the revenue.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A transparent market where brokers can buy and sell company stock, e.g. the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stock Exchange

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a stock exchange to information about the ticker symbols of companies that are traded on the exchange.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Companies Traded

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a stock exchange to a location that is covered by the exchange, e.g. the Stock Exchange of Thailand is related to the country of Thailand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Primary Regions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The financial service of advising and assisting in the filling out and filing of local or federal income tax returns.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tax Preparation Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all car insurance policies. Car insurance is a type of insurance protecting against vehicle damage and/or bodily damage from traffic accidents and the ensuing liability. Most regions and some car loans require specific terms of vehicle insurance.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Auto Insurance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all car loans. Car loans are loans that are secured by vehicles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Vehicle Loan
